# With a real DOMAIN (and ports 80/443 reachable) Caddy provisions a Let's Encrypt
# certificate automatically. With the default `localhost`, Caddy issues a local self-signed
# cert via its internal CA — HTTPS still works (the browser warns about the unknown CA),
# which is enough for the app's Secure cookies.
{$DOMAIN:localhost} {
	reverse_proxy app:8080
}
